Day 13 â€“ CSS Colors and Backgrounds

CSS allows changing text and background colors.
color property sets text color.
background-color sets the background.
You can use color names, HEX codes, or RGB values.
Example:

body { background-color: #f0f0f0; color: #333333; }


background-image adds images, and background-repeat controls repetition.
Proper use of colors improves readability and design.
